Ad Text:
Company Description

At Colliers, we are enterprising. What sets us apart is not what we do, but how we do it. Our people are passionate, take personal responsibility and always do what’s right for our clients, people and communities. We accelerate their success by empowering them to think and act differently to drive exceptional results. 

With circa 9,000 experts in Asia Pacific, our enterprising culture and decentralised operating model allows us to act with speed in local markets, seizing opportunities to innovate and accelerate the success of our clients and our people.

Our collaborative culture sets us apart. We help experts become true specialists and provide the long-term structure and platform to accelerate their success.

Job Description

We’re seeking a Business Analyst to deliver a new IT solution for our Residential Project Marketing team. This 6-month contract is central to implementing a unified CRM and stock management system that integrates marketing automation, reporting, and customer journey visibility.

You’ll work closely with internal stakeholders and a third‑party solution provider to ensure the system is designed to requirements, thoroughly tested, and successfully implemented.

Key Responsibilities

Collaborate with business teams to capture workflows, pain points, and requirements.
Define solution architecture and plan CRM, stock management, contract workflow, and reporting customisations.
Support data migration, including extraction, validation, preparation, and upload.
Facilitate workshops, project meetings, and stakeholder alignment with the software provider.
Develop and coordinate test plans, track issues, and ensure resolution.
Assist with training delivery and create user guides for staff adoption.
Qualifications
3+ years as a Business Analyst in IT or digital transformation.
Experience delivering projects independently or in a project manager role.
Strong knowledge of real estate operations, especially residential sales.
Familiarity with CRM systems and property technology platforms.
Skilled in business analysis tools and Agile methodologies.
Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement, and documentation skills.
Bachelor’s degree in Information Systems, Property, Business, or related field (preferred).
Additional Information

We foster an environment in which everyone at Colliers feels respected and comfortable bringing their authentic selves to do their best work. It’s our people who set us apart and we actively recruit people who represent the diversity of the communities in which we operate. We take great pride in doing what’s right and operating in ways that benefit the business, our people, our clients, our communities, and the environment.

Experts join experts, and we welcome you to join us as we lead the industry into the future.

Please apply with your CV or call Lydia Masterson on 02 9257 0357 for more information.

Please be advised that applications will only be accepted directly rather than via recruitment agencies.

#LI-LM1

·         Build and enhance Dyno Nobel’s enterprise financial planning capability

·         Own the group’s corporate financial model and long‑term forecasting

·         Operate as a senior individual contributor with enterprise‑wide impact

At Dyno Nobel Limited, our people vision is to unlock our people capability and culture to create safe, inclusive and high‑performing teams on the ground.

The Role

As the Global FP&A Manager, you will play a critical role in shaping Dyno Nobel’s financial future. This is a standalone role with no direct reports, ideal for someone who thrives as a senior individual contributor and enjoys full ownership of complex, high‑value work.

You will partner closely with senior leaders across the organisation, providing independent commercial insight that informs executive decision‑making, capital allocation and long‑term value creation.

You will:

Lead the group budgeting, forecasting and business planning processes

Maintain integrated short‑ and long‑term forecasts (P&L, balance sheet, cash flow)

Own and enhance the group’s core corporate financial model

Conduct scenario, sensitivity and stress testing for strategic initiatives

Act as a key authority on balance sheet capacity, leverage and funding headroom

Prepare high‑quality insights and materials for Executive and Board forums

What you’ll bring

You must be committed to positively contributing to our safe, inclusive and high‑performance culture.

CA or CPA qualification

Experience in FP&A, corporate finance or investment banking

Advanced Excel and financial modelling capability

Strong understanding of integrated financial statements and valuation methodologies

Ability to translate complex analysis into clear, commercially relevant insights

Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills across global teams

If you are excited about the role and think you have what it takes but your experience doesn’t align 100%, we still want to hear from you.

Benefits to you

We are a team focused on safety, inclusion and high performance.

18 weeks paid parental leave for primary carer, 3 weeks for secondary carer

Superannuation paid on unpaid parental leave, up to 12 months

Hybrid work model (three office days, two remote days)

Salary packaging options

Confidential employee assistance program

Mental health and wellbeing program

Options to purchase annual leave (where eligible)

Various corporate discount programs

Workplace giving charitable scheme

Opportunities for career progression through succession planning and development reviews

About Us

As an ASX100 company and industry frontrunner, Dyno Nobel Limited offers diverse career opportunities globally, emphasising safety, inclusivity and high performance. Our passionate team of almost 6,000 employees work across our global operations to manufacture and distribute industrial explosives and industrial chemicals.

Leveraging diversity through inclusion

At Dyno Nobel Limited, we believe in the strength of diversity and inclusivity, fostering an environment that is safe, equitable and embraces differences to enhance performance. We go beyond ‘diversity of thought’, valuing people from a variety of backgrounds and encouraging applicants from diverse identities.

Our commitment extends to helping our team excel at work while achieving a harmonious work‑life balance. To support this, we offer a range of work styles and a paid parental leave policy, ensuring our team thrives both personally and professionally.

What our employees say

“Everyone has been very welcoming which has been lovely!”

“We have a good collaborative team, a team that is always striving to improve and a good culture.”

About our process

Our recruitment process typically involves a Teams or face‑to‑face interview, reference checks and a medical check. It may also include a site visit and psychometric testing.

We value diversity, equity and inclusion and are committed to ensuring a welcoming experience for all candidates. We encourage you to share any support or adjustments you need to be at your best during our recruitment process. If you have any questions before or during your application, please get in touch at careers@dynonobel.com.

(Please note: this email is for enquiries only — we cannot accept resumes via email.)

Job Title: Telco Transformation Consultant, Lean Six Sigma Black Belt
Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Job Title

Telco Transformation Consultant - Lean Six Sigma Black Belt
Contract until 30 June

Overview

A leading global consultancy is in discussions with a major telecommunications client regarding several transformation roles expected to commence in Feb.

These roles focus on delivering measurable operational and customer outcomes across core telecommunications domains. The consultant will apply Lean Six Sigma Black Belt methodologies to drive sustainable improvement across complex telco environments.

Key Responsibilities

The consultant will be responsible for:

Leading end-to-end process improvement and transformation initiatives within telecommunications environments

Applying Lean Six Sigma Black Belt methodology to diagnose complex problems and deliver sustainable solutions

Conducting root cause analysis, process mapping, value stream analysis, and benefits quantification

Partnering with senior stakeholders to shape scope, define requirements, and build delivery roadmaps

Facilitating workshops and working sessions to drive alignment and momentum

Producing clear insights, recommendations, and implementation plans

Supporting change adoption across operational and enterprise customer-facing functions

Ensuring delivery aligns to strategic objectives and improves performance, cost, or customer experience

Essential Requirements

Applications will only be considered if you meet all of the following:

Currently based in Sydney, NSW

Lean Six Sigma Black Belt, with demonstrated experience leading real-world improvement programs

Telecommunications industry experience, ideally within one or both of the following domains:

Network operations

Without both Black Belt certification and relevant telco experience, candidates will not progress.

Additional Experience and Skills

Strong problem-solving capability, comfortable working through ambiguity and complexity

Proven consulting skillset, including structured thinking, stakeholder management, and executive-level communication

Track record delivering measurable outcomes in operational excellence, transformation, or continuous improvement

Ability to influence across technical and non-technical teams

Excellent documentation skills, with the ability to produce clear, decision-ready outputs

Desirable

Experience in large-scale telco transformation programs

Exposure to service assurance, network delivery, enterprise customer lifecycle, or managed services

Background in consulting or professional services environments

To Note: we can only consider applicants who are Sydney-based and hold a Lean Six Sigma Black Belt with telecommunications network experience.

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high‑performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.


Your New Role


We're looking for a Senior Analyst - Risk Enablement to join our Group Risk team on an 18-month fixed term contract, based in Melbourne with hybrid working.

Reporting to the Senior Manager, Risk Strategy & Enablement, this role offers variety and exposure across multiple risk domains. You'll provide second line support to subject matter experts and leaders, contributing to both business-as-usual activities and strategic initiatives. Your work will span a variety of activities to support Group Risk colleagues implementing a risk transformation project either through their project or key business as usual deliverables.

Key duties include but are not limited to:

Support Group Risk SMEs and Leads with BAU tasks across five risk departments.
Support implementation and embedment of risk transformation projects.
Assist with controls testing, risk assessments, and policy updates.
Perform data analysis and reporting to inform decision-making.
Maintain GRC records and coordinate workshops, training, and policy reviews.
Develop training materials and collateral for risk initiatives.
Manage the Group Risk Enablement workplan and associated reporting.
Coordinate monthly communications such as the 'In the Know' Bulletin and 3 Lines Forum.
Promote compliance and risk awareness across the organisation.


What You'll Need



3+ years' experience in risk management within financial services or consulting.
Strong understanding of risk and control practices, frameworks, and assurance activities.
Experience in risk assessments, control reviews, and risk reporting.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office, especially Excel and PowerPoint.
Critical thinking and analytical skills with a continuous improvement mindset.
Excellent communication skills and ability to build collaborative relationships.
Tertiary qualifications in Business, Commerce, Law or a related field.
Experience with RSA Archer GRC tool and/or PowerBI.
Exposure to risk in change programs.
Accreditation or willingness to obtain accreditation in Risk Management (e.g., RMIA or GIA).
Ability to translate regulatory requirements (e.g., APRA) into practical business outcomes.


Life at AustralianSuper


AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.


What's Next


Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.

AustralianSuper uses AI to review resumes and conduct initial phone interviews. This involves processing your resume, cover letter, and voice recording in Australia and the USA to help assess your suitability for the applied role. When invited to an AI phone screening, you may opt for a traditional phone screening instead.

For information on how we handle your personal data, please refer to our Candidate Privacy Notice: https://www.australiansuper.com/careers/candidate-privacy-notice

Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper's Talent Acquisition team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you.

Ad Text:
We are seeking an experienced Principal Business Analyst to support a large-scale enterprise SAP re-platforming and upgrade program within a complex, statewide operating environment. This role sits within a critical corporate systems function responsible for workforce management, payroll, finance and logistics platforms that support a large and diverse public sector workforce.
 
You will join a major Enterprise SAP Re-platforming Program, focused on transitioning core SAP ERP solutions from ageing infrastructure to modern S/4HANA Cloud-based platforms. The program spans HR/Payroll, Workforce Management, Finance, Business and Logistics solutions and underpins a broader multi-year corporate business systems roadmap.
Key program objectives include:

Delivering a proof of concept for HR/Payroll migration and upgrade
Re-platforming SAP ECC6 HR/Payroll and Workforce Management solutions
Upgrading SAP Finance, Business and Logistics to S/4HANA Cloud
Establishing a contemporary, scalable technology foundation to support future enterprise delivery
The Role:
As Principal Business Analyst, you will lead the identification, analysis and documentation of business processes and requirements across multiple stakeholder groups. You will work closely with program leadership, technical teams and business representatives to ensure enterprise SAP solutions are fit-for-purpose, efficient and aligned to organisational outcomes.
 
Key Responsibilities:

Lead and facilitate business requirements gathering across complex, multi-stakeholder environments
Analyse current and future-state business processes within SAP HR/Payroll, Workforce Management and Finance domains
Produce high-quality business analysis documentation suitable for both technical and non-technical audiences
Provide expert advice on optimising enterprise workforce management and payroll processes
Support process re-engineering activities, including identifying policy and procedural impacts
Contribute to project, release and delivery planning activities
Provide strategic and operational advice to influence solution design and delivery outcomes
Lead, mentor and support multidisciplinary teams
Ensure compliance with information security, quality management and public sector governance standards
Support delivery activities that may require occasional out-of-hours work to meet critical milestones
About You:
You are a senior Business Analyst with deep experience operating in large, enterprise or public sector environments and can confidently navigate complexity, scale and governance.

Demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst working with:
SAP S/4HANA Finance, Business & Logistics, and/or
SAP ECC6 HR/Payroll, and/or
Infor WFM / Rostering solutions
Strong process analysis and documentation skills
Proven ability to engage and influence senior stakeholders
Experience working on ERP upgrades, re-platforming or transformation programs
A pragmatic, delivery-focused mindset with strong attention to quality and detail
If you're an experienced SAP Business Analyst looking to contribute to a high-impact enterprise transformation in a short-term engagement, we'd love to hear from you. khair@sharpandcarter.com.au

build out strategy, roadmap and development of data ecosystem

extensive experience leading BI and data engineering teams, including hands-on skills in ETL and pipeline build and API integration

Click on the 'Apply' button or email your CV to sahuja@fourquarters.com.au

Data Analytics Consultant

Agile Insights is one of Australia’s fastest growing Microsoft Data and AI partners. We work with government, enterprise, and commercial organisations across the country to modernise data platforms with Microsoft Fabric, accelerate AI adoption, and deliver high-impact analytics solutions that create meaningful outcomes for customers.

As we continue to scale nationally, we are expanding our consulting team with a Data Analytics Consultant who brings strong capability across both Azure data engineering and Power BI. This is a hands-on role suited to someone who enjoys solving complex data challenges, building modern analytics solutions, and working directly with customers to help them succeed.

About the role

Reporting to a Practice Lead, you will work across the full delivery lifecycle—from data ingestion and modelling through to semantic layers and Power BI reporting. You will design and develop Azure-based data pipelines, build scalable datasets, and deliver high-quality reporting experiences that drive real business value. You will work closely with customers to understand their challenges and help shape the solutions that support their data and analytics strategy.

Key Responsibilities

Shape end-to-end analytics architectures spanning ingestion, transformation, semantic modelling, and reporting.
Design and build high-performance Fabric data pipelines, lakehouses/warehouses, and Power BI datasets, reports, and dashboards following best practice standards.
Apply data governance, security, lineage, and quality practices across Azure/Fabric and Power BI ecosystems, including workspace administration and controls within Power BI.
Partner with customers to understand requirements and translate them into clear technical designs.
Support testing, validation, and deployment of data and analytics solutions.
Contribute to internal frameworks, accelerators, and delivery standards as part of a growing practice.
Collaborate closely with peers, share knowledge, and continuously evolve your technical capability.
Contribute to DevOps practices such as CI/CD for Fabric pipelines, semantic models, and Power BI assets.

About you

You are an experienced data and analytics professional who enjoys working across data engineering, semantic modelling, and BI/reporting.

You understand how to design scalable data solutions, build robust models, and create reporting experiences that support real business outcomes. You are curious, collaborative, and comfortable working directly with customers in a consulting environment.

You will bring

Strong hands-on experience with Azure data engineering tools such as Data Factory, Synapse, Data Lake, or Fabric.
Strong Power BI capability including DAX, Power Query, data modelling, and design principles.
Confidence working with SQL and modern data platform concepts.
Experience translating business requirements into effective data and reporting solutions.
Strong understanding of how data engineering, semantic modelling, and BI/reporting fit together in modern analytics architectures.
Experience designing solutions that balance performance, governance, usability, and maintainability.
Familiarity with data governance concepts such as workspace design, security models, access patterns, and content certification.
Ability to advise customers on best practices across modelling, data architecture, and visualisation.
A balanced skillset across data engineering, semantic modelling, and business intelligence, with the ability to work confidently across the full data and analytics lifecycle.
Clear communication skills and the ability to engage with technical and non-technical stakeholders.
A focus on quality, consistency, and continuous improvement.
An interest in Microsoft Fabric and modern analytics approaches.
Experience with Python or Power Platform is beneficial but not essential.

Why Agile Insights

You will join a team with deep technical capability, strong alignment with Microsoft, and an ambition to become Australia’s leading Data and AI partner. You will work on complex and interesting projects, gain exposure to modern Azure and Fabric architectures, and be supported by senior consultants who are experts in their field. You will have the opportunity to grow your skills, contribute to a high-performing practice, and play a meaningful role in the delivery of solutions that genuinely impact our customers.

Boral is the largest integrated construction materials supplier in Australia, producing and selling a broad range of construction materials, including aggregates, cement, concrete, asphalt, and recycled materials. Employing more than 9,000 employees and contractors, Boral's operations span across 367 operating and distribution sites nationally.

 

About the Role:

An exciting opportunity for an experienced Financial Analyst has become available to join our Laboratory Services Team based in our North Ryde office. Reporting directly to the Head of Laboratory Services, the purpose of your role is to partner with key business leaders to provide financial support, commercial focus and to drive superior commercial and financial outcomes.

This includes developing the financial literacy within the business, driving business performance including supporting Boral's Continuous and Value Improvement Programs, providing independent financial perspectives to senior leaders, and supporting customer and general commercial arrangements.

 

Daily Duties:

Acts independently to apply comprehensive understanding of the business environment and objectives developing solutions while providing guidance others.
Acts as a strategist / catalyst, providing financial leadership for the division and stimulating behaviours to create value through achieving strategic and financial objectives.
Uses comprehensive knowledge and skills to act independently while guiding and training others on supporting business decisions with professional interpretations of financial information.
Uses comprehensive knowledge and skills to work independently while providing guidance and training to others on planning, organizing, prioritizing and overseeing activities to efficiently meet business objectives
Works without supervision and provides technical guidance when required on developing appropriate plans or performing necessary actions based on recommendations and requirements.
Identifies, assesses, prioritizes and manages risks without supervision and provides technical guidance when required.
Uses comprehensive knowledge and skills to work independently on costing, budgeting and finance tasks while providing guidance and training to others.
Uses comprehensive knowledge and skills to work independently while providing guidance and training to others on analysing data from multiple sources to draw appropriate conclusions and make suitable recommendations.
Works independently and provides guidance and training to others on analysing data trends for use in reports to help guide decision making.

 

About you:

Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent) in Commerce, Business, Finance or Economics
Wide and deep experience providing expert advice on financial outcomes pertaining to end to end sales, logistics and operations in large and complex industrial or manufacturing businesses
Wide and deep experience providing expert advice on financial outcomes pertaining to end to end sales, logistics and operations in large and complex industrial or manufacturing businesses
Experience of planning, managing and organizing resources within short / medium timescales within the overall policy framework.

 

Boral values and is committed to creating a diverse working environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All suitable applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, disability or age.

Company description:



Department of Communities and Justice



Job description:



Manager Standardised Evaluation Analysis

Location - Parramatta/Hybrid working (or another DCJ office location, with some self-funded travel to Parramatta required).

Employment type - Temporary full-time role up to 30 June 2028

Salary - $149,739.00 pa - $173,174.00 pa, plus employer's contribution to superannuation and annual leave loading

About the role

The Manager, Standardised Evaluation Analysis (StEvAn) will oversee and manage the delivery of the StEvAn on behalf of the NSW Government.

Part of the NSW Government Actuary, the StEvAn is the NSW Government's sophisticated and innovative new approach to human services evaluation to build the evidence base for what works.

What you'll do

The successful candidate will be required to manage the StEvAn team and overarching project to deliver outcome evaluation result for a variety of programs and initiatives. It will require a combination of technical skills in evaluation along with superior project management skills. Familiarity with Python and database design is important as this role will require the ability to span the full spectrum of the standardised evaluation process from conventional outcome evaluation design, database management through to overseeing the implementation of the analysis software code which has been designed in house.

The role is responsible for overseeing outcome evaluation design, data analysis, and reporting, ensuring methodological rigour, data integrity, and alignment with governance and strategic priorities. It provides expert advice to senior stakeholders, translating complex findings into clear, actionable insights.

The Manager also leads and develops a technically-diverse team of analysts, driving best practice, continuous improvement, and a collaborative, high-performing culture while working closely with stakeholders to strengthen evaluation capability and outcomes.

The role has a whole-of-government remit. It is part of the NSW Government Actuary, a specialist team of about 30 analysts and evaluation professionals.

What we're looking for

In addition to the essential requirements outlined in the role description, the ideal candidate for the Manager, Standardised Evaluation Analysis role will bring a strong blend of technical expertise, project management, strategic thinking, and people leadership.

They will demonstrate intermediate to advanced capability in Python programming and database design, with a proven ability to develop, manage, and optimise evaluation frameworks and analytical pipelines. The candidate will have experience in evaluation design, including defining metrics, ensuring methodological rigour, and translating complex data into clear, actionable insights for diverse stakeholders.

The ideal candidate will be capable of leading multiple workstreams, setting clear priorities, managing risks, and delivering outcomes within agreed timeframes. They will be comfortable working in complex environments, balancing competing demands while maintaining a strong focus on quality, consistency, and governance.

As a people leader, they will foster a collaborative, inclusive, and high-performing team culture. They will be skilled at mentoring and developing staff, promoting best practice, and driving continuous improvement in analytical capability and processes.

Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills are essential. The candidate will be able to confidently present findings, influence decision-making, and build productive relationships across technical and non-technical audiences.

Above all, the ideal candidate will be self-motivated, outcomes-focused, and committed to continuous improvement, with a strong sense of accountability and a passion for using data and evaluation to support evidence-based decision-making.
